article.headline: Air Force 81, Arkansas-Pine Bluff 45
article.story: AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. (AP) -- Jacob Burschi and Tim Anderson each scored 13 points as Air Force beat Arkansas-Pine Bluff 81-45 Friday night to extend their home winning streak to 18. Nick Welch scored 12 points and added a team-best eight rebounds in his first game since missing all of last season with injuries. Air Force held Arkansas-Pine Bluff to 0-for-11 shooting to start the game as the Falcons (1-0) jumped to a 16-0 lead. The Lions (0-1) scored their first basket at the 12:33 mark of the first half. Matt McCraw added 10 points, while Burtschi dished out a career-high six assists and added six rebounds. William Byrd led Arkansas-Pine Bluff with 17 points and was the only Lion in double figures. Arkansas-Pine Bluff finished the game shooting 32.7 percent from the field and 2-of-17 (11.7 percent) from 3-point range.
